[2] Comment on cVDPV3 and OPV3
Date: Thu 31 Mar 2022
From: Prof. T Jacob John <tjacobjohn@yahoo.co.in> [edited]


Regarding: PRO/EDR> Poliomyelitis update (14): Israel, RFI 20220331.8702310
MOH daily update [29 Mar 2022]:

Jerusalem and its environs:
6 "fully confirmed diseased cases"
1 "highly suspected diseased case"
All 7 are in unvaccinated patients.
There is also one "partially vaccinated" new case "under investigation."

My comments:
On 24 Oct 2019, WHO had announced the Certification of the Global Eradication of Poliovirus type 3 (https://www.who.int/news-room/feature-stories/detail/two-out-of-three-wild-poliovirus-strains-eradicated). The last case of polio due to wild poliovirus type 3 was in Nigeria, in 2012. Now 10 years later an outbreak of polio due to type 3 virus derived from oral polio vaccine is being reported in and around Jerusalem, Israel.

It is widely known since 1964, that among the 3 vaccine virus types, the most common cause of vaccine-associated paralytic polio (VAPP) is type 3. The benefit-risk ratio of OPV type 3 became negative in 2012. Three years of absence is the norm to declare eradication; hence, from January 2016 the continued use of vaccine type 3 became ethically wrong. For some strange reason, VAPP is not counted, by defining it non-polio acute flaccid paralysis. The Jerusalem outbreak is a stark reminder that public health interventions must strictly follow biomedical ethics. The use of vaccine virus type 3 is to be stopped forthwith, globally. Once the source is clipped, the outbreak can be controlled with the inactivated poliovirus vaccine (IPV). It is remarkable that all children with confirmed polio were unvaccinated.

--
Communicated by:
T Jacob John
(Retired) Professor of Clinical Virology
Christian Medical College, Vellore, India

[Once again Prof. T Jacob John is spot on -- reminding us of the history of polio eradication and the crucial decision points necessary for preventing cVDPV. ProMED is grateful that Prof. T Jacob John shares these observations with us and our subscribers. - Mod.MPP]
